<!-- Player embedded -->                      <p class="introduction" id="story_continues_1">President Vladimir Putin is making his first visit to Crimea since Russia annexed it from Ukraine in March.</p>&#13;
        <p>He told crowds marking the 1945 Soviet victory over the Nazis that Crimea had shown loyalty to a "historical truth" in choosing to be part of Russia. </p>&#13;
        <p>The Kiev government protested at the visit, calling it a "gross violation of Ukraine's sovereignty".</p>&#13;
        <p>Kiev also reported that more than 20 people had died in a security operation against separatists in Mariupol.</p>&#13;
